se xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531357\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531357\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qob1665702760448.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qob1665702760448.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qob1665702760448.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qob1665702760448\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Implementing an OS Service\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface enables you use an operating system service to send commands and return output from an operating system.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"qob1665702760448__context_w5970ab1b5b1_w5971ab1b5_w5972ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"qob1665702760448__topic_d36173e1_d36174e1_d36175e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qob1665702760448__p_d36176e1_d36177e1_d36178e1\">To create and use an OS service:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qob1665702760448__li_d18482e1_d18483e1_d18484e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qob1665702760448__p_d36179e1_d36180e1_d36181e1\">Create a signature for an operating system\n               service with the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Implementation Type</span> set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Operating\n                  System Command</code>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Two default, non-editable operations are available, <code class=\"ph codeph\">COMMAND</code> and\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">COMMANDOUT</code>. </div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qob1665702760448__li_d18485e1_d18486e1_d18487e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qob1665702760448__p_d36182e1_d36183e1_d36184e1\">In the calling component, call the OS service\n               using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> statement.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\"> For example, if you created a component called OSUNIX:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">activate \"OSUNIX\".COMMAND(\"at -fm myscript now\")\nactivate \"OSUNIX\".COMMANDOUT(\"ls -l mydir\", $LISTING$)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qob1665702760448__p_d36185e1_d36186e1_d36187e1\">Output is passed to the\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">$LISTING$</code> variable.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qob1665702760448__li_d18488e1_d18489e1_d18490e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qob1665702760448__p_d36188e1_d36189e1_d36190e1\">In your application’s assignment file, specify a\n               path that directs the operating system component to the operating system server. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$SERVER1:=TCP:PHOENIX|leda|?|CSV\n[SERVICES_EXEC]\nOSUNIX=$SERVER1:OSUNIX</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzx1665702678830.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define a Component Signature</a><p>Use the Signature Editor to create or modify component signatures. Signatures of Uniface components are automatically generated during compilation. Signatures of non-Uniface components can be created or imported.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gbz1665702543976.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>[PATHS]</a><p>Use the [PATHS] section of the assignment file to define paths to network and database connectors, which connect to a Uniface Server, DBMS, or to another path. Path assignments can include path-to-connector assignments and path-to-path assignments.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujx1665702543107.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>[SERVICES_EXEC]</a><p>Use the [SERVICES_EXEC] section of the assignment file to direct the execution of service components to a network path, COM, or SOAP connector, and to redefine the behavior of COM and SOAP connectors for specific components.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/guj1665702895376.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Operating System Commands</a><p>Uniface enables you to pass commands to the operating system and catch the returned output using the COMMAND and COMMANDOUT operations.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531357\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531357\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Implementing an OS Service Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Implementing an OS Service Uniface enables you use an operating system service to send commands and return output from an operating system. To create and use an OS service: Create a signature for an operating system service with the Implementation Type set to Operating System Command . Two default, non-editable operations are available, COMMAND and COMMANDOUT . In the calling component, call the OS service using the activate statement. For example, if you created a component called OSUNIX: activate \"OSUNIX\".COMMAND(\"at -fm myscript now\") activate \"OSUNIX\".COMMANDOUT(\"ls -l mydir\", $LISTING$) Copy Output is passed to the $LISTING$ variable. In your application’s assignment file, specify a path that directs the operating system component to the operating system server. For example: [PATHS] $SERVER1:=TCP:PHOENIX|leda|?|CSV [SERVICES_EXEC] OSUNIX=$SERVER1:OSUNIX Copy Related Links Define a Component Signature Use the Signature Editor to create or modify component signatures. Signatures of Uniface components are automatically generated during compilation. Signatures of non-Uniface components can be created or imported. [PATHS] Use the [PATHS] section of the assignment file to define paths to network and database connectors, which connect to a Uniface Server, DBMS, or to another path. Path assignments can include path-to-connector assignments and path-to-path assignments. [SERVICES_EXEC] Use the [SERVICES_EXEC] section of the assignment file to direct the execution of service components to a network path, COM, or SOAP connector, and to redefine the behavior of COM and SOAP connectors for specific components. Operating System Commands Uniface enables you to pass commands to the operating system and catch the returned output using the COMMAND and COMMANDOUT operations. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}